						               													<description>A collection of miniature wargaming rules that are only 2 pages (A4) long: the Pz8 rules are intended for a small table, ideally with &amp;quot;micro&amp;quot; models, play fast (from 30' to 1 hour) and are solo friendly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Classic miniature wargaming mechanics are used, in the simplest possible way, but trying to keep a minimum degree of realism and allowing historical tactics. All rules use D6 for resolving combat. Some of the rules, like the WW2 and Modern land, use rulers for movement and weapons ranges, while others use a grid system, like the WW2 and Modern aerial (hexes) the WW1(squares) and the WW2 naval (large areas). Representational scales vary from 1 base of miniatures = 1 Battalion or 1 Platoon, to 1 model = 1 aircraft or ship, again depending on the rules set.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Available as a free .pdf the Pz8 Wargaming Rules Collection includes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Pz8 WW2 rules &amp;#10;- Pz8 1950-75 rules &amp;#10;- Pz8 1975-2010 rules &amp;#10;- Pz8 Sci-Fi rules &amp;#10;- Pz8 WW2 Divisional rules &amp;#10;- Pz8 1939-41 Naval rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 WW2 Coastal rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 Space rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 WW1 Divisional rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 1935-65 &amp;amp; WW1 Aerial rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 1965-75 Aerial rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 Colonial Wargame rules&amp;#10;- Pz8 Fantasy Wargame rules&amp;#10;- Legio VIII Ancient / Medieval Wargame rules&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
